# AI Behavior & Coding Rules

Please refer to and strictly enforce the guidelines defined in [DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md](file:///Users/intersamrt/Documents/backend/DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md).

Key directives:

1. Do not use unnecessary, complex shell commands (this is a single-developer project; keep commands simple and standard).
2. If code needs to be completed, write explicit, detailed `// TODO:` comments explaining what needs to be done.
3. Keep the codebase minimal and clean. Do not over-engineer or add speculative utilities (adhere to YAGNI).
4. Use standard TypeScript naming conventions and verify all method calls match their signatures exactly.
